counterproductive.中释: 反生产的；使达不到预期目标的
counterproductive.英释: Something that is counterproductive achieves the opposite result from the one that you want to achieve

industrialization.英释: when a country or place develops a lot of industry

indistinguishable.中释: 不能区别的，不能辨别的；不易察觉的
indistinguishable.英释: If one thing is indistinguishable from another, the two things are so similar that it is difficult to know which is which

telecommunication.中释: 电讯；[通信] 远程通信；无线电通讯
telecommunication.英释: the telegraphic or telephonic communication of audio, video, or digital information over a distance by means of radio waves, optical signals, etc, or along a transmission line
